OL,3,CCouncillors resign from Labour party
OL,4,Cover 'bullying' claims
OL,6,F"Sadly, over a recent period, senior
OL,7,Fparty officials have attempted to
OL,8,Fimpose their ideas at a local level. I
OL,9,Fwas elected to serve the public, not
OL,10,Fparty officials."
OL,12,FCouncillor Yvonne Tennant added: "At a
OL,13,Ftime when 14 years of Tory cuts are
OL,14,Faffecting local people across Pendle,
OL,15,Fthe Labour Party leadership should be
OL,16,Fallowing local hard-working
OL,17,Fcouncillors the opportunity to
OL,18,Fchallenge the Tories.
OL,20,F"Instead, colleagues are being
OL,21,Fhindered from fulfilling their roles."
