OL,3,CCouncillors resign from Labour party
OL,4,Cover 'bullying' claims
OL,6,FAmong those who have quit the Labour
OL,7,Fparty Councillor Mohammed Iqbal who
OL,8,Fwas suspended from the party for 18
OL,9,Fmonths over claims he made antisemitic
OL,10,Fcomments at a meeting.
OL,12,FMr Iqbal, who denies the claims, said:
OL,13,F"I joined the Labour Party over 30
OL,14,Fyears ago and have always been
OL,15,Fencouraged to speak out on issues.
OL,17,F"However, senior figures within the
OL,18,Fparty are attempting to stifle free
OL,19,Fspeech and threaten dedicated
OL,20,Fcouncillors with removal as candidates.
